      • reloadTopLevelPage

        public <T extends TopLevelPage> T reloadTopLevelPage(Class<T> pageClass)
        Invalidate cached page, and return a fresh TopLevelPage with newly initialized WebElements. This method does not do a Browser Refresh of the page. It does: Invalidate the cache. Initialize the current page again by loading webelements and running page load hooks
        Parameters:
        pageClass - - the class of the current Page

      • loadSubPage

        public <T extends SubPage> T loadSubPage(Class<T> pageClass)
        Load a sub page. No caching is used for SubPage's.
        Parameters:
        pageClass - - the class of the SubPage that is currently present on the DOM in the browser to load.

      • loadTopLevelPage

        public <T extends TopLevelPage> T loadTopLevelPage(Class<T> pageClass)
        If the current page is still valid, and the URL hasn't changed, and the class given as input is assignable from the cached page, THEN return the cached page and avoid re-initializing web elements and running page hooks.

        Otherwise, invalidate the cache and load as normal.

        Parameters:
        pageClass - - the class of the current Page
